@startuml claude-worker-pool-architecture
!include _standard-style.puml

title Claude CLI Worker Pool — Architecture (@rapid/llm-proxy)\nTwo-tier claude-code dispatch: persistent stream-JSON workers + execFile overflow\nv7.3 (Phases 62-63)

top to bottom direction

rectangle "LLM Proxy Bridge (proxy-bridge/server.mjs)" as bridge {
  component [POST /api/complete\n(dispatcher)] as complete <<api>>
  component [claude-code dispatch\n(two-tier)] as dispatch <<core>>
  complete -down-> dispatch : model is a\nclaude-code tier
}

package "Worker Pool (proxy-bridge/worker-pool.mjs)" as poolpkg {
  component [WorkerPool] as pool <<core>>

  component "workersByKey\nMap<key, ClaudeWorker[]>" as map <<storage>>

  package "key = model :: sha256(systemPrompt)[:16]" as keypkg {
    component [ClaudeWorker #1\n(busy)] as w1 <<cli>>
    component [ClaudeWorker #2\n(free)] as w2 <<cli>>
  }

  component [crash cooldown\n_crashesByKey + _recordCrash] as cooldown <<util>>
  component [LRU prompt-cap\n_enforcePromptCap + _touch] as lru <<util>>

  pool -down-> map : lazy-spawn /\nacquire free worker
  map -down-> keypkg
  pool ..> cooldown : record exits,\ngate storming keys
  pool ..> lru : evict least-recently\n-used prompt pool
}

component [completeClaudeCodeViaCLI\n(execFile one-shot overflow)] as overflow <<cli>>

cloud "Anthropic (Claude Max)" as cloud {
  component [claude -p subprocess\n--input-format stream-json\n--output-format stream-json] as cli <<external>>
  component [api.anthropic.com\n(via CLI session)] as api <<external>>
}

' Two-tier routing
dispatch SYNC_LINE pool : Tier 1 (fast path)\nWorkerPool.complete(body, abortSignal, overflowFn)
dispatch -down-> overflow : Tier 2 (overflow)\nall workers busy OR key in cooldown\nOR LLM_PROXY_DISABLE_WORKER_POOL=1
pool .down.> overflow : overflowFn (passed in)\nwhen no free worker

' Worker to subprocess
w1 SYNC_LINE cli : stream-JSON request\nover persistent stdin/stdout
w2 SYNC_LINE cli
overflow SYNC_LINE api : one-shot `claude -p`\nper request (cold)
cli -down-> api

note right of pool
  **WorkerPool.complete(body, abortSignal, overflowFn)**
  1. key = (model x systemPrompt)
  2. cooldown gate -> overflow if key storming
  3. acquire free worker (find !busy) or
     lazy-spawn up to LLM_PROXY_WORKER_POOL_SIZE
  4. no free worker -> overflowFn (execFile)
  5. abort: in-flight -> SIGTERM + _disposeAndDrop;
     queued -> abortQueuedJob (dequeue + reject)
end note

note right of keypkg
  **ClaudeWorker** — persistent `claude -p` subprocess
  - concurrency-1 with a FIFO queue
  - per-request timeout (LLM_PROXY_WORKER_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS)
  - request-generation guard drops stray late results
  - _writeGuarded routes EPIPE to the exit reaper (RETRYABLE)
  - recycles after MAX_REQUESTS / MAX_INPUT_TOKENS
  - unref'd idle timer evicts after LLM_PROXY_WORKER_IDLE_MS
end note

note bottom of overflow
  **Why keep the execFile path?**
  Overflow absorbs bursts beyond pool size, storming keys in
  crash-cooldown, and the GUARD-01 escape hatch
  (LLM_PROXY_DISABLE_WORKER_POOL=1) — a cold one-shot
  `claude -p` per request, ~10-14s, always available.
end note

note bottom of cooldown
  **Crash cooldown (WLIFE-03)**
  >= LLM_PROXY_WORKER_CRASH_THRESHOLD crashes within
  LLM_PROXY_WORKER_CRASH_WINDOW_MS -> route the key to
  overflow until the window elapses, then lazily respawn.
  Stops a broken key spin-looping spawn->crash->RETRYABLE.
end note

@enduml
